      "writtenOn": "2020-09-11T17:18:32Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think I started doing this due to c++11 and copy-initialization from braced lists (see https://abseil.io/tips/142 ). Mostly I wanted to avoid not stating the name SkFILEStream and the user creating one in an opaque way like putting \"{file, 10}\" in an argument list. Of course, in the time since this was done originally, we generally now take std::unique_ptr\u003cSkStreamXXX\u003e most places and never take an SkFILEStream by value so it\u0027s probably a bit moot, but I do like the idea of enforcing the name being used since this class is going to implicitly take ownership of the FILE.",
      "parentUuid": "0a43aa37_8f3c2a8a",
