      "writtenOn": "2020-09-11T17:18:32Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "So this signature is a bit of a hack, there is already a constructor which takes (std::shared_ptr\u003cFILE\u003e, size_t, size_t) with the middle one being \u0027endOffset\u0027 instead of \u0027size\u0027. So if we delay the creation of the shared_ptr I don\u0027t need to add an extra argument to differentiate. The real issue is that \u0027length\u0027 and \u0027offset\u0027 don\u0027t have semantically different types.",
